com.travelbank.knit

Class KnitPresenter2<I,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.travelbank.knit.KnitPresenter<T>
      • com.travelbank.knit.KnitPresenter2<I,T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MemoryEntity, MessageReceiver, NativeViewCallbacks, PresenterInterface

    public class KnitPresenter2<I,T>
extends KnitPresenter<T>
    KnitPresenter object that allows the use of Interactors. Presenter classes that are exposed to the developer by Knit. These need to be annotated with Presenter and a target view class to be registered with Knit. All KnitPresenters will have a InternalPresenter counterpart that is actually used by Knit framework to manage these. Views that are annotated with KnitView will automatically have their contracts created by Knit. Those contracts should be be given to this class. Contracts will be have all non-android, public & package-private methods of the view exposed.
